<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,841,1120]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,877,902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Arista absent in males (
<collectionCode box="[591,669,878,902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45">MSSC</collectionCode>
) (
<figureCitation box="[692,755,878,902]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1269,1292]" captionTargetBox="[382,1207,750,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[376,1211,741,1248]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhaphium srilankensis sp. nov.: first flagellomere. A. male. B. female (scale bar = 0.1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[744,755,878,902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A); first flagellomere with dense pubescence, 
<number box="[1267,1281,879,902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45" value="7.0">7</number>
times as long as basal width, with acute apex; in females the arista is subapical and the first flagellomere is twice as long as basal width (
<figureCitation box="[230,293,950,974]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1269,1292]" captionTargetBox="[382,1207,750,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[376,1211,741,1248]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhaphium srilankensis sp. nov.: first flagellomere. A. male. B. female (scale bar = 0.1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[282,293,950,974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B); mesonotum with purplish longitudinal stripe between dc rows in both sexes; ac small and biseriate; 
<number box="[1422,1436,950,974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45" value="6.0">6</number>
strong dc present; 
<number box="[357,371,985,1009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
strong marginal scutellars present, without lateral setae or hairs; hind coxa with a strong lateral seta; mid femur with an anterior and a posterior preapical seta, fore and hind femora without preapicals; veins R 
<number box="[1366,1374,1037,1051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1383,1390,1037,1051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="45" value="5.0">5</number>
and M subparallel in distal section. Male hypopygium partially exposed and visible under postabdomen (see species description for detailed description of the hypopygium).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
